launcher.title: Tools
launcher.description: List of tools. This is a useful demo.

infohub_tools_checksum.YOU_CAN_GENERATE_A_CHECKSUM_FROM_THE_DAT: You can generate a checksum from the data you enter.
infohub_tools_checksum.YOU_CAN_SELECT_WHAT_NODE_WILL_GENERATE_T: You can select what node will generate the checksum.
infohub_tools_checksum.YOU_CAN_SELECT_WHAT_TYPE_OF_CHECKSUM_YOU: You can select what type of checksum you want.
infohub_tools_checksum.IS_USED_IN_SWEDEN_AS_A_PERSONAL_IDENTIFI: Is used in sweden as a personal identifier or a company identifier.
infohub_tools_checksum.YOU_CAN_ENTER_A_PERSONNUMMER_IN_THIS_FOR: You can enter a personnummer in this format:
infohub_tools_checksum.YY_=_TWO_DIGIT_YEAR,_MM_=_TWO_DIGIT_MONT: Yy = two digit year, mm = two digit month, dd = two digit day of month,
infohub_tools_checksum.THE_CHECKSUM_WILL_CALCULATE_THE_FOURTH_(: The checksum will calculate the fourth (last) digit.
infohub_tools_checksum.SELECT_WHAT_CHECKSUM_METHOD_YOU_WANT_TO_: Select what checksum method you want to use
infohub_tools_checksum.WHAT_NODE_PLUGIN_DO_YOU_WANT_TO_PRODUCE_: What node plugin do you want to produce the checksum?
infohub_tools_checksum.WHAT_TYPE_OF_CHECKSUM_DO_YOU_WANT_TO_CRE: What type of checksum do you want to create?
infohub_tools_checksum.YOUR_DATA_YOU_WANT_A_CHECKSUM_FOR_KEY: Your data you want a checksum for

infohub_tools_compress.YOU_CAN_WRITE_YOUR_TEXT_IN_THE_TEXT_BOX_: You can write your text in the text box : compress the data.
infohub_tools_compress.YOU_CAN_SELECT_WHAT_NODE_AND_METHOD_YOU_: You can select what node and method you want to use to compress the data.
infohub_tools_compress.CLICK_THE_BUTTON:_COMPRESS._CLICK_ON:_DE: Click the button: compress. Click on: decompress, to see the result.
infohub_tools_compress.REMOVE_THE_TEXT_YOU_WROTE._NOW_CLICK_THE: Remove the text you wrote. Now click the button: decompress.
infohub_tools_compress.WHAT_NODE_SHOULD_COMPRESS_YOUR_DATA?_KEY: What node should compress your data?
infohub_tools_compress.WHAT_COMPRESSION_METHOD_DO_YOU_WANT_TO_U: What compression method do you want to use?
infohub_tools_compress.WHAT_NODE_SHOULD_DECOMPRESS_YOUR_DATA?_K: What node should decompress your data?
infohub_tools_compress.WHAT_DECOMPRESSION_METHOD_DO_YOU_WANT_TO: What decompression method do you want to use?

infohub_tools_encrypt.THIS_TOOL_CAN_ENCRYPT_AND_DECRYPT_YOUR_T: This tool can encrypt and decrypt your text
infohub_tools_encrypt.SELECT_WHAT_ENCRYPT_METHOD_YOU_WANT_TO_U: Select what encrypt method you want to use
infohub_tools_encrypt.WHAT_NODE_PLUGIN_DO_YOU_WANT_TO_ENCRYPT\: What node plugin do you want to encrypt/decrypt on?
infohub_tools_encrypt.WHAT_TYPE_OF_ENCRYPTION_METHOD_DO_YOU_WA: What type of encryption method do you want to use?

infohub_tools_package.WITH_THIS_TOOL_YOU_CAN_VIEW_DATA_FROM_TH: With this tool you can view data from the package property messages encoded.
infohub_tools_package.SEE_YOUR_BROWSER_NETWORK_TAB_IN_DEVELOPE: See your browser network tab in developer tools.
infohub_tools_package.PASTE_A_STRING_FROM_MESSAGES_ENCODED_KEY: Paste a string from messages encoded
infohub_tools_package.WILL_SHOW_THE_DECODED_PRETTY_JSON_KEY: Will show the decoded pretty json

infohub_tools_password.PASSWORD_LENGTH_=_LENGTH_OF_THE_PASSWORD: Password length = length of the passwords you want.
infohub_tools_password.0_(DEFAULT)_GIVES_YOU_A_RANDOM_LENGTH_16: 0 (default) gives you a random length 16-64 characters.
infohub_tools_password.MAX_GROUP_NUMBER_=_NUMBERS_OF_GROUPS_TO_: Max group number = numbers of groups to include in the password.
infohub_tools_password.DEFAULT_MAX_GROUP_NUMBER_=_4_(0-4)_SOME_: Default max group number = 4 (0-4) some sites do not allow spaces, then set max group number = 3.
infohub_tools_password.SOME_SITES_DO_NOT_ALLOW_SPECIAL_CHARACTE: Some sites do not allow special characters, then set max group number = 2.
infohub_tools_password.SELECT_WHAT_PASSWORD_FORMAT_YOU_WANT_TO_: Select what password format you want to use
infohub_tools_password.WHAT_NODE_PLUGIN_DO_YOU_WANT_TO_PRODUCE_: What node plugin do you want to produce the checksum?
infohub_tools_password.WHAT_GROUPS_DO_YOU_WANT_IN_YOUR_PASSWORD: What groups do you want in your password?
infohub_tools_password.WHAT_PASSWORD_LENGTH_DO_YOU_WANT?_KEY: What password length do you want?

infohub_tools_random.WITH_THIS_TOOL_YOU_CAN_GET_THE_CURRENT_R: With this tool you can get the current random in different formats
infohub_tools_random.SELECT_WHAT_RANDOM_FORMAT_YOU_WANT_TO_US: Select what random format you want to use
infohub_tools_random.WHAT_NODE_PLUGIN_DO_YOU_WANT_TO_PRODUCE_: What node plugin do you want to produce the checksum?

infohub_tools_testcall.WITH_THIS_TOOL_YOU_CAN_WRITE_TEST_CALLS_: With this tool you can write test calls and trigger functions.
infohub_tools_testcall.PRACTICAL_IF_YOU_WANT_TO_DEBUG_A_SPECIFI: Practical if you want to debug a specific function.
infohub_tools_testcall.WRITE_YOUR_TEST_CALL_AND_SEND_IT_KEY: Write your test call and send it
infohub_tools_testcall.SELECT_A_TEMPLATE_FOR_THE_CALL_YOU_WANT_: Select a template for the call you want
infohub_tools_testcall.THE_CALL_YOU_WANT_TO_MAKE_KEY: The call you want to make

infohub_tools_time.WITH_THIS_TOOL_YOU_CAN_GET_THE_CURRENT_T: With this tool you can get the current time in different formats
infohub_tools_time.OBSERVE_THAT_THE_SERVER_PHP_PLUGIN_MUST_: Observe that the server php plugin must know about your time zone.
infohub_tools_time.SEE_THE_DOCUMENTATION_FOR_INFOHUB_TIME_H: See the documentation for infohub time how to change that
infohub_tools_time.SELECT_WHAT_TIME_FORMAT_YOU_WANT_TO_USE_: Select what time format you want to use
infohub_tools_time.WHAT_NODE_PLUGIN_DO_YOU_WANT_TO_PRODUCE_: What node plugin do you want to produce the checksum?
infohub_tools_time.WHAT_TIME_FORMAT_DO_YOU_WANT?_KEY: What time format do you want?
infohub_tools_time.WILL_SHOW_THE_TIME_IN_THE_RIGHT_FORMAT_K: Will show the time in the right format

infohub_tools_uuid.YOU_CAN_GENERATE_A_UUID4_FROM_THE_CLIENT: You can generate a uuid4 from the client plugin or from the server plugin
infohub_tools_uuid.WHAT_NODE_PLUGIN_DO_YOU_WANT_TO_PRODUCE_: What node plugin do you want to produce the uuids?
infohub_tools_uuid.WHAT_VERSION_(FLAVOUR)_OF_THE_UUID_DO_YO: What version (flavour) of the uuid do you want?
